A small plane crashed in a residential street near a middle school Thursday in Hilltop Township, north of Philadelphia, killing two people on board, news outlets reported.
The National Transportation Safety Board identified the aircraft as a Beech 35-C33 and 
said in a tweet
 that the crash was being investigated. 
News outlets said the crash happened about 5 p.m. and the victims have not been identified. Aerial footage showed the planeâ€™s charred fuselage covered by a blue tarp and surrounded by emergency vehicles Thursday evening. 
Hilltown Township Police Chief Christopher Engelhart praised the pilot for avoiding hitting any homes in the crash, calling him a hero, 
WCAU-TV reported. 
The aircraft went down about 200 feet (60 meters) from the edge of the Pennridge Central Middle School campus.
